DISCIPLINARY CASES

2002-2149. Stark Cty. Bar Assn. v. Hare.

Upon consideration of the motion filed by counsel for respondent for leave to withdraw as counsel and the motion for extension of time to file objections,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that the motions be, and hereby are, granted.

IT IS FURTHER ORDERED by the court that, pursuant to S.Ct.Prac.R. XIV(3), respondent’s objections and brief in support shall be filed on or before January 21, 2003.
